  <h1>Divine Trust System</h1>
  <h2>Trust Law Forms Library</h2>

  <hr>

  <p>
    Below are the official forms required for constructing, filing, or managing your trust under the Divine Trust System. Each form includes a brief description, intended use, and associated preparation cost. You may fill them out digitally or request assistance from a Trust Architect.
  </p>

  <div class="form-section">
    <div class="form-title">1. Declaration of Trust</div>
    <div class="description">
      The foundational document that declares the formation of the trust and outlines its core intent. This is the spiritual and lawful "birth certificate" of your trust.
    </div>
    <div class="price">Cost: $1,000</div>
  </div>

  <div class="form-section">
    <div class="form-title">2. Trust Indenture Agreement</div>
    <div class="description">
      Defines the detailed terms of administration, trustee powers, beneficiary rights, asset control, and duration of the trust. Required for enforceability.
    </div>
    <div class="price">Cost: $1,200</div>
  </div>

  <div class="form-section">
    <div class="form-title">3. Trust Registration Form</div>
    <div class="description">
      Official recordation of the trust with the Divine Trust Network. Allows assignment of trust ID, celestial record entry, and legal timestamping.
    </div>
    <div class="price">Cost: $250</div>
  </div>

  <div class="form-section">
    <div class="form-title">4. Notice of Trust (Public Notice Form)</div>
    <div class="description">
      Issues public or private notice to all jurisdictions acknowledging the trustâ€™s existence and authority. May be published in the record portal.
    </div>
    <div class="price">Cost: $150</div>
  </div>

  <div class="form-section">
    <div class="form-title">5. Trustee Appointment & Affidavit</div>
    <div class="description">
      Legally binds your appointed trustee(s) to the duties and principles of your trust, including loyalty, fiduciary duty, and oath of performance.
    </div>
    <div class="price">Cost: $300</div>
  </div>

  <div class="form-section">
    <div class="form-title">6. Schedule of Assets Form</div>
    <div class="description">
      Itemizes all assets to be held, governed, or protected under the trust. Includes real estate, vehicles, intellectual property, financial holdings, etc.
    </div>
    <div class="price">Cost: $200</div>
  </div>

  <div class="form-section">
    <div class="form-title">7. Beneficiary Declaration Form</div>
    <div class="description">
      Official form for listing your beneficiaries, their rights, terms of inheritance, and applicable contingencies.
    </div>
    <div class="price">Cost: $150</div>
  </div>

  <div class="form-section">
    <div class="form-title">8. Trust Amendment or Revocation Form</div>
    <div class="description">
      Used to change, update, or dissolve the terms or structure of an existing trust. Only valid if allowed under your Indenture.
    </div>
    <div class="price">Cost: $300</div>
  </div>

  <div class="form-section">
    <div class="form-title">9. Certificate of Trust Existence</div>
    <div class="description">
      A simplified summary that verifies the existence and status of the trust for banks, institutions, or legal notices. Optional.
    </div>
    <div class="price">Cost: $100</div>
  </div>

  <div class="form-section">
    <div class="form-title">10. Trust Resignation / Appointment Transfer Form</div>
    <div class="description">
      Allows resignation of a trustee and formal transfer of position or responsibilities to a new one. Optional use in case of health, travel, or death.
    </div>
    <div class="price">Cost: $250</div>
  </div>

